  "prompt": "I am Nepali citizen havn Nepali pasport, want to travel to Dubai with my family from India, do v need nythng else apart frm pasport and visa?",
  "response": "To travel from India to Dubai as a Nepali citizen, you'll typically need:\n\n1. Valid Nepali Passport\n2. Dubai Visa (tourist or visit visa)\n3. Proof of return ticket\n4. Hotel reservation/accommodation details\n5. Sufficient funds for your stay\n6. Travel insurance (recommended)\n7. Passport should be valid for at least 6 months from date of entry\n\nAdditional documents you might need:\n- Bank statements\n- Proof of employment\n- Invitation letter (if applicable)\n\nNote:\n- Apply for visa through authorized travel agency or UAE embassy\n- Check specific visa requirements as they can change\n- Ensure all family members have individual visas\n- Check COVID-related travel guidelines before departure\n\nRecommended steps:\n1. Confirm visa requirements\n2. Arrange necessary documents\n3. Apply for visa in advance\n4. Check travel insurance options\n5. Prepare copies of important documents\n\nWould you like more specific details about the visa application process?",
